# Notes

## Initial hypotheses

- Dust accumulation.
- Flat cable failure.
- Key matrix failure.
- PCB oxidation.
- Main board failure.

---

## Findings

- No obvious burned components.
- Possible oxidation observed.
- Flat cables visually intact.
- Key mechanism appeared mechanically normal.
- Most failures appear to be electrical rather than mechanical.

---

## Lessons learned

- Internal structure of an electronic keyboard.
- Function of flat cables.
- Rubber contact operation.
- PCB inspection.
- Reverse engineering methodology.
- Importance of documentation during a project.

